File: A South African Airways carrier is parked in a bay on the tarmac. JOHANNESBURG – The South African Airways cancelled its flights between Johannesburg and Hong Kong on Monday. Hong Kong's Airport Authority has suspended all flights. READ: 'Dancing aunties' spark new Hong Kong protest Protesters are demonstrating at the airport after a female protester was shot in the eye. It's the fourth day that protesters are gathering at the airport. “Based on the suspension of air services, SAA’s operations between Hong Kong and Johannesburg for 12 August 2019 have been cancelled,” said SAA spokesperson Tlali Tlali. The following flights have been affected: SA287 12 August 2019 Hong Kong to Johannesburg | Scheduled time of departure 23h55 SA286 12 August Johannesburg to Hong Kong | Scheduled time of departure 17h35